  <title>Setup <app>Git</app></title>

  <p>To use <app>Git</app> on your distribution, you would need to install and configure it. The following sections will show you how to:</p>

  <section id="git-pacman">
    <title>Install <app>Git</app></title>

    <p><app>Git</app> is available on <app>Pacman</app> as <app>git-VERSION</app>, where <em>VERSION</em> could be anything of the format <em>x.x.x.x-x</em>, for example <var>git-1.8.5.2-1</var>. Type and run <cmd>sudo pacman -S git</cmd>. You should be seeing terminal output similar to:</p>

